snippet.textDisplay:
There’s only 4 types of pozole I have tried. Red, green and white pozole. The green one is done with regular yellow American corn (in Mexico we only have white one, but we also use canned yellow).

Love topping mine with cabbage, tomatoes, onion, radishes, and lime juice. My mom makes some salsa for it using the corn, oil and Chile de árbol.

Oh! Next time use just one Chile ancho, it gives it a great color to the broth too!

And in pure authentic fashion, human meat was used. As it was a post battle food made of human flesh. Then came the turkey, then the rest.
snippet.textOriginal:
There’s only 4 types of pozole I have tried. Red, green and white pozole. The green one is done with regular yellow American corn (in Mexico we only have white one, but we also use canned yellow).

Oh! Next time use just one Chile ancho, it gives it a great color to the broth too!

And in pure authentic fashion, human meat was used. As it was a post battle food made of human flesh. Then came the turkey, then the rest.
